{"id":47606749942,"slug":"a-salmon-is-a-fish-that-swims-upstream-to-its-hone","type":"text","date":"2013-04-10 07:17:48 GMT","timestamp":1365578268,"format":"html","tags":[],"highlighted":[],"note_count":0,"title":null,"body":"<p>A salmon is a fish that swims upstream to its hone waters. So too do the &ldquo;salmon&rdquo; of Indian highways, which see fit to occupy any lane they please while driving against the flow of traffic. While most salmon are simply two-wheelers on the shoulder we have seen rickshaws, cars, and even a huge truck in the innermost incoming lane.</p>"}